    <h2 id="why-keto">What Keto Gummies Actually Do (and What They Cannot)</h2>

    <p>The ketogenic diet works by restricting carbohydrates to fewer than 20-50g daily, forcing the liver to convert stored fat into ketone bodies (BHB, acetoacetate, acetone) for energy. This metabolic shift — called nutritional ketosis — typically takes 2-7 days and is accompanied by the dreaded "keto flu": headaches, fatigue, brain fog, irritability, and muscle cramps caused by electrolyte depletion and the body's adjustment to fat-based fuel. Keto gummies are designed to ease this transition and support ongoing ketosis, not replace the dietary carb restriction that drives actual ketone production.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
      <span class="key-stat-num">2-7</span>
      <p class="key-stat-txt">days is the typical timeframe to enter nutritional ketosis after restricting carbs to fewer than 50g daily. The <strong>"keto flu" during this transition causes 30-40% of new keto dieters to quit within the first week</strong>. Exogenous BHB gummies can reduce keto flu severity by providing supplemental ketones while your body adapts to producing its own.</p>
    </div>

    <p>There are three categories of "keto gummies" on the market, and understanding the differences is critical: (1) BHB gummies contain actual exogenous ketone bodies that measurably elevate blood ketone levels, (2) ACV gummies claim keto benefits through apple cider vinegar's effects on blood sugar, and (3) generic "keto" labeled gummies that contain no ketone-supporting ingredients whatsoever — they are regular gummies with keto marketing. Our evaluation focuses on products that contain genuine keto-supporting ingredients (BHB, MCT, electrolytes) at meaningful doses.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="zap" size={22} /></div><strong>BHB — Exogenous Ketones</strong><p>Beta-hydroxybutyrate is the primary circulating ketone body. Supplemental BHB provides ready-to-use ketone energy, reduces keto flu symptoms during transition, and helps maintain ketone levels after occasional carb intake. The brain can immediately use BHB for fuel.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="droplet" size={22} /></div><strong>MCT Oil — Ketone Precursor</strong><p>Medium-chain triglycerides are rapidly converted to ketones by the liver without requiring full beta-oxidation. MCT oil in keto gummies provides a fast ketone boost and sustained energy. C8 (caprylic acid) is the most ketogenic MCT fraction.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="fitness" size={22} /></div><strong>Electrolytes — Keto Flu Prevention</strong><p>The low-insulin state of ketosis increases sodium and potassium excretion through the kidneys. Electrolyte depletion causes the majority of keto flu symptoms. Keto gummies with sodium, potassium, and magnesium directly address this root cause.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="flask" size={22} /></div><strong>ACV — Blood Sugar Support</strong><p>Apple cider vinegar contains acetic acid, which may reduce post-meal blood sugar spikes by 20-30% and improve insulin sensitivity. This supports ketosis indirectly by minimizing glucose availability that would suppress ketone production.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <div class="warn-box-ico"><Icon name="warning" size={18} /></div>
      <p><strong>No keto gummy will put you in ketosis if you are still eating high carbs.</strong> Exogenous ketones provide supplemental fuel, but nutritional ketosis requires dietary carb restriction (fewer than 50g/day). Be skeptical of products claiming "effortless ketosis" or "keto without dieting" — these are marketing claims, not physiological realities. Keto gummies are tools that support the ketogenic diet, not replacements for it.</p>
    </div>

